<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,258,284]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[856,1003,259,285]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A." box="[1048,1355,259,285]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="373 - 396" refId="ref31297" refString="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A. (2009) The Muscidae (Diptera: Brachycera: Muscomorpha) of south-western Saudi Arabia. Fauna of Arabia, 24, 373 - 396." type="journal article" year="2009">Dawah &amp; Abdullah (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. It was described from Ruwenzori in 
<collectingCountry box="[486,573,295,321]" name="Uganda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Uganda</collectingCountry>
from a single male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,430,330,357]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Biological remarks.</emphasis>
Reared during January and February from shoots of 
<taxonomicName authority="Desv." authorityName="Desv." box="[1008,1364,331,357]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Rhytachne" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rottboellioides">
<emphasis box="[1008,1294,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Rhytachne rottboellioides</emphasis>
Desv.
</taxonomicName>
growing on the margins of Samaru lake in 
<collectingCountry box="[577,661,367,393]" name="Nigeria" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Deeming, J. C." box="[676,845,367,393]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="133 - 190" refId="ref31515" refString="Deeming, J. C. (1971) Some species of Atherigona Rondani (Diptera: Muscidae) from Northern Nigeria, with special reference to those injurious to cereal crops. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 61, 133 - 190. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300057527" type="journal article" year="1971">Deeming 1971</bibRefCitation>
) and from cultivated tef (
<taxonomicName box="[1135,1288,367,393]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eragrostis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tef">
<emphasis box="[1135,1288,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Eragrostis tef</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in 
<collectingCountry box="[1341,1436,367,393]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nigus, C. &amp; Damte, T." box="[159,406,403,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref34450" refString="Nigus, C. &amp; Damte, T. (2018) Identification of tef shoot fly species from major tef (Eragrostis tef [Zucc] Trotter growing areas of [sic] Ethiopian. African Journal of Insects, 5 (3), 181 - 184." type="journal article" year="2018">Nigus &amp; Damte 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
